reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Close Call with the Dryer, but Still a Win
reviews.reviewText: I recently added a pair of dark camel linen pants to my wardrobe, and despite a minor hiccup in the laundry department, these bottoms have quickly become a favorite. The initial love affair began with the impeccable fit, flattering silhouette, and the delightful inclusion of pockets – a real game-changer.The fit is nothing short of perfection. The pants hug in all the right places without feeling restrictive, and the slightly oversized design adds a touch of laid-back comfort. The flattering cut enhances my silhouette, making these linen wonders my go-to choice for both casual outings and more polished affairs.Now, onto the accidental laundry misadventure. Despite my usual commitment to air-drying, these pants found themselves in the clutches of the dryer. To my dismay, they emerged a good 3+ inches shorter. Panic aside, the silver lining was the initial oversized fit – a savior that allowed me room for this unexpected mishap.What could have been a major fashion tragedy turned out to be a minor inconvenience. The pants, now slightly cropped, surprisingly retained their chic look and comfort. The linen material gracefully adapted to the change, maintaining its quality and feel.I'm relieved to report that, even after the unintentional encounter with the dryer, my love for these linen pants has only deepened. They remain a wardrobe staple, and I've learned to embrace their new cropped charm. A testament to their durability and timeless style, these pants have proven that a small laundry blunder doesn't have to spell the end for a well-loved piece.In conclusion, these dark camel linen pants are a wardrobe win. From the initial flawless fit to the accidental shrinkage and subsequent adaptation, they've earned their place as a versatile and resilient favorite. If you're on the hunt for stylish, comfortable, and forgiving linen pants, these are the ones to snag – just be sure to keep them out of the dryer!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute and Casual Pants
reviews.reviewText: It’s now October and I have been wearing these pants (plus I bought a beige pair) all summer. They were perfect! Comfortable and cool but also provided a chic and casual look. They have maintained their quality and aren’t showing any wear. I just bought a pair in black for Fall. Definitely recommend.I have been looking for some cute and casual pants I can wear during this coming summer. I ordered the teal in small and I’m happy with them out of the packaging. I think these will work well for what I want from them. They fit great (nice and loose without looking too baggy). The length is just right for wearing sandals or flats. The fabric is light and breathable without feeling too cheap or flimsy. The teal color is more of a denim blue than teal. I was a little disappointed with the color difference (wanted a more green teal like the photo) but when I put them on my boyfriend immediately complemented me on the color (he loves blue). It’s a nice neutral blue that will go with a lot of tops. For sizing reference, I am 5’6”, 117 lbs and usually wear a small. They fit true to size. I would recommend and may purchase another color. I haven’t washed them yet. I will update if they shrink or fall apart after a few washes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 23, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I would’ve given it five stars but they really do shrink if you put them in the dryer .I’m gonna order a second pair because they’re so comfy. I’ll just be more cautious when laundering moving forward.That being said, my first pair , I ordered in an extra large, and so as they have shrunk, they still fit. Before I washed them, as I was walking up the stairs I had to be careful to kind of lift the leg or I could step on the cuff and trip. Now they’re a little at the ankle with one time going through the dryer, but they still fit very comfortably around the waist, the hip, the butt,.Even though I could get away with a large, I will still order an extra large again, because the comfort was really pajama like, and if I accidentally threw them into the dryer again, I know they’ll still fit, but they’ll just be shorter. It’s odd that the rest of it must’ve shrunk, but it still fits very comfortably.These pants are well-made. They’re fun and comfortable and cute. A great alternative to shorts during the hot summer months easily dressed up or just with a cute tank top and very casual flip-flops.I’m not sure how to really explain how unbelievably comfortable they are how, it’s like getting away with wearing pajamas in public that are really flattering and cute.

reviews.reviewText: Great pants to bring on vacation. They stretch and shrink and hit with washing and drying but that hasn’t been an issue. Nice and light weight. Comfortable and cute for vacation or a day out

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 24, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I really wanted to love these pants. At first they were great, nice and long, the fabric was super comfy and flowy. They were cute and flattering. I washed cold, gentle, and laid flat to dry… the legs shrunk up by an inch or so. Washed them again, they shrunk up again. They’re still comfy and I still wear them, but they’re more like ‘casual mom on the go’ pants rather than ‘cute mom who still has some style’ pants.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Cute pants, very beachy! I ended up rolling the waste a couple times because they were a little long. Material is not as soft as I would have hoped but still very comfortable!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Cute but they SHRINK!!!
reviews.reviewText: I thought I could ignore the other reviews and get by with washing these pants on cold and hang drying them. They still shrunk wayyyyy too much. The hip and thigh area shrunk but was still manageable, however, the length went from a little past my ankles to half way up my shin. I got one wear so I am disappointed to say the least. Should’ve listened to other reviewers!
